Russia managed hardly five years ago to put its vision on a direct alliance between Russia and the rich Western states with high gas consumption, whose bearings are approaching its end.
"This gas pipeline is a component of our partnership with Russia, a new artery that organically connects us", confirmed François Fillon at the solemn opening of this pipeline and demonstrated at what point the great gas contracts of things are both political and economic.
This explains all the wide smiles of the leaders of Gazprom present in the large number of Lubmin, the gas supply place.
The construction of this pipeline is also an important technical act.
Submarine pipes are made of steel equipped with concrete caps to be protected from sea vessels.
It rests on the bottom of the sea at an average depth of 200 m.
During his construction, it was necessary to avoid mining fields coming from World War II.
"For the safety of them, almost a hundred had to be removed or destroyed", says Jens Müller, spokesman Nord Stream.
It was also necessary to increase the measures to protect fauna and flora.
The pipe itself is a long metal snake weighing like 242 Eiffelovek, which is nowhere interrupted at all its length, neither valves nor maintenance stations.
One control platform was to be built near Sweden, but the project manager rejected it when the Swedish were only few wishes to see the Russian state society, as it continued to settle at their shore.
"In case of failures, we stop gas flow in less than 1 minute," says Jens Müller.
In case of insolvent gas contained in the gas pipeline, it shall escape into the air.
But this case is considered to be unlikely by the builders, for the weeds were designed to result in sealing once in 100,000 years.
The control of the state of the gas pipeline from the outside is carried out by a sub-sea robot drawn by a ship while the inside of the gas pipeline is controlled by a device which circulates inside.
This cigar shape device with a diameter of 1 meter is introduced into the inside of the pipe and is pushed by gas.
In the target of three days the speed of 3 m/s will provide accurate information on possible deformation of metal parts.
The remote gas pipeline has been designed to function for fifty years without having to be the least repair.
The circulation of gas is simply secured by pressure.
The value of this pressure is 200 bar at the start and 100 bar in the target.
Five companies have joined forces to implement this project.
The head of Gazprom remains a share of 51%.
E.ON and BASF (15.5% each) as well as Gasunia and the French GDF Suez Group (9% each).
These five companies created a joint undertaking called Nord Stream entrusted with the construction and operation of the pipeline.
